---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Automation Tools for RevOps & GTM Teams"
  description="The best automation tools for RevOps and GTM teams — tested and reviewed. Workflow automation, CRM enrichment, and revenue intelligence."
>
  <!-- Affiliate disclosure -->
  <div class="container--wide" style="padding-top:2rem;">
    <div class="affiliate-notice">
      <strong>Affiliate Disclosure:</strong> Some links on this page are affiliate links. If you sign up or purchase through them, we earn a commission at no extra cost to you. We only list tools we'd genuinely recommend to a fellow RevOps practitioner — our editorial opinions are not influenced by affiliate relationships.
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="tools-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hero-eyebrow">Tools &middot; Reviews &middot; Recommendations</div>
      <h1>The best automation tools for RevOps and GTM teams — tested and reviewed</h1>
      <p>
        Curated picks across workflow automation, CRM, enrichment, and revenue intelligence —
        with honest takes on where each tool fits and when to use it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Workflow Automation -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container--wide">
      <div class="tools-category">
        <h2 class="tools-category-heading">Workflow Automation</h2>
        <p class="tools-category-sub">The middleware layer that connects your stack and runs your GTM playbooks.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tool-grid">

        <div class="tool-card">
          <div class="tool-card-header">
            <h3>Make</h3>
            <span class="tool-badge tool-badge--free">Free tier available</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            Make (formerly Integromat) is the best-in-class automation platform for RevOps teams
            that need complex logic, data transformation, and multi-path workflows. More powerful
            than Zapier at a fraction of the cost, with a visual canvas that makes it easy to
            reason about even the most complex flows.
          </p>
          <a href="AFFILIATE_LINK_PLACEHOLDER" class="btn btn--primary tool-cta" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            Try Make &rarr;
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="tool-card">
          <div class="tool-card-header">
            <h3>n8n</h3>
            <span class="tool-badge tool-badge--free">Free (self-hosted)</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            n8n is an open-source workflow automation tool you can self-host for full data control
            and no per-operation pricing. It's ideal for engineering-forward GTM teams that want
            Make-level power without ongoing platform costs.
          </p>
          <a href="AFFILIATE_LINK_PLACEHOLDER" class="btn btn--ghost tool-cta" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            Explore n8n &rarr;
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="tool-card">
          <div class="tool-card-header">
            <h3>Zapier</h3>
            <span class="tool-badge tool-badge--free">Free tier available</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            Zapier is the fastest way to get an automation off the ground, with thousands of
            pre-built integrations and an intuitive trigger-action model. Best for simple, linear
            workflows and teams that need to move fast without a technical setup.
          </p>
          <a href="AFFILIATE_LINK_PLACEHOLDER" class="btn btn--ghost tool-cta" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            Try Zapier &rarr;
          </a>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CRM & Enrichment -->
  <section class="section" style="border-top:1px solid var(--border);">
    <div class="container--wide">
      <div class="tools-category">
        <h2 class="tools-category-heading">CRM &amp; Enrichment</h2>
        <p class="tools-category-sub">The systems of record and data layer that power your GTM motion.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tool-grid">

        <div class="tool-card">
          <div class="tool-card-header">
            <h3>HubSpot</h3>
            <span class="tool-badge tool-badge--free">Free tier available</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            HubSpot is the CRM at the center of most modern GTM stacks, with built-in workflow
            automation that handles lead routing, deal stage triggers, and sequences out of the box.
            The free tier is genuinely useful; paid tiers unlock the automation depth RevOps teams
            actually need.
          </p>
          <a href="AFFILIATE_LINK_PLACEHOLDER" class="btn btn--primary tool-cta" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            Try HubSpot &rarr;
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="tool-card">
          <div class="tool-card-header">
            <h3>Clay</h3>
            <span class="tool-badge">Paid</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            Clay combines a spreadsheet interface with 50+ enrichment data sources to help you
            build targeted, personalized outbound lists at scale. If your SDR team is manually
            researching accounts, Clay is the highest-leverage tool you're probably not using yet.
          </p>
          <a href="AFFILIATE_LINK_PLACEHOLDER" class="btn btn--ghost tool-cta" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            Try Clay &rarr;
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="tool-card">
          <div class="tool-card-header">
            <h3>Apollo.io</h3>
            <span class="tool-badge tool-badge--free">Free tier available</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            Apollo combines a 275M+ contact database with built-in email sequencing, making it a
            one-stop shop for outbound GTM teams. The enrichment API also integrates cleanly with
            HubSpot for keeping CRM data current without manual data entry.
          </p>
          <a href="AFFILIATE_LINK_PLACEHOLDER" class="btn btn--ghost tool-cta" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            Try Apollo &rarr;
          </a>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Revenue Intelligence -->
  <section class="section" style="border-top:1px solid var(--border);">
    <div class="container--wide">
      <div class="tools-category">
        <h2 class="tools-category-heading">Revenue Intelligence</h2>
        <p class="tools-category-sub">Conversation intelligence and forecasting tools that make pipeline data actionable.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tool-grid">

        <div class="tool-card">
          <div class="tool-card-header">
            <h3>Gong</h3>
            <span class="tool-badge">Paid</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            Gong records, transcribes, and analyzes your sales calls using AI to surface deal risks,
            coaching moments, and pipeline forecasts. RevOps teams use it to build repeatable
            processes from what actually works in the field.
          </p>
          <a href="AFFILIATE_LINK_PLACEHOLDER" class="btn btn--ghost tool-cta" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            Learn More &rarr;
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="tool-card">
          <div class="tool-card-header">
            <h3>Chorus</h3>
            <span class="tool-badge">Paid</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            Chorus by ZoomInfo captures conversation intelligence from sales calls and syncs
            insights directly into your CRM. It's particularly strong for teams that need to
            understand which talk tracks convert and which stall deals at each stage.
          </p>
          <a href="AFFILIATE_LINK_PLACEHOLDER" class="btn btn--ghost tool-cta" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            Learn More &rarr;
          </a>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
